git pull is a fundamental command used to synchronize the local repository with the remote repository. It combines two actions: fetching updates from the remote repository (git fetch) and merging those updates into the current branch (git merge).

git pull to:
Fetch the latest changes made by other developers or automation tools.
Ensure the local repository reflects the latest configurations or code changes.

